Class Client

  • java.lang.Object
    • Client
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BotBase
    public class Client
extends java.lang.Object
    Connects, sends, and receives messages with a server at a specified address / port.

        public Client​(java.net.InetAddress remoteAddress,
              int remotePort)
        Constructs a new Client instance.
        Parameters:
        remoteAddress - The address of the server.
        remotePort - The port to connect to. (Server needs to be actively listening for connections on this port)

    • Method Detail

      • Connected

        public boolean Connected()
        Determines if this client is connected to a server.
        Returns:
        Whether the client is connected.

      • TryConnect

        public boolean TryConnect()
        Tries to connect to the server with the address / port given at instantiation. Can only connect to one server at a time.
        Returns:
        Whether we successfully connected to the server. Returns false if already connected.

      • Disconnect

        public void Disconnect()
        Disconnects from the currently connected server, disposes of any resources used. Can reconnect to a new server once disconnected. Calling this multiple times has no effect.

      • CloseConnection

        private void CloseConnection()
        Closes connection with the connected server. A new connection can be made after closing this one. Calling this multiple times has no effect. Be aware that this call does not deal with remaining resources used.

      • StartListeningForMessages

        public void StartListeningForMessages()
        Starts listening for messages from the server. Calling this does not block the thread it is called from. Calling this multiple times has no effect.

      • OnMessageReceived

        public void OnMessageReceived​(java.lang.String message)
        Logic for when we receive a message.
        Parameters:
        message - The message received.

      • StopListeningForMessages

        public void StopListeningForMessages()
        Stops listening for messages from the connected server. Calling this multiple times has no effect.

      • StartSendingMessages

        public void StartSendingMessages()
        Starts treating inputs from the terminal as messages to be sent to the connected server. Calling this multiple times has no effect.

      • SendMessage

        public void SendMessage​(java.lang.String message)
        Sends a message to the server.s
        Parameters:
        message - The message to send.

      • StopSendingMessages

        public void StopSendingMessages()
        Stops sending terminal inputs as messages to the server. Calling this multiple times has no effect.

      • SetFirstResponse

        public void SetFirstResponse​(java.lang.String firstResponse)
        Sets the first response that should be sent to the server when connceting.
        Parameters:
        firstResponse - The response to send.
